TY  - JOUR
T1  - Skewness Sentiment and Market Anomalies
AU  - Kumar, Alok
AU  - Motahari, Mehrshad
AU  - Taffler, Richard J.
Y1  - 2023/08/29
PY  - 2023
DA  - 2024/07/01
N1  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.2023.4898
DO  - 10.1287/mnsc.2023.4898
T2  - Management Science
JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - 4328
EP  - 4356
VL  - 70
IS  - 7
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - This study demonstrates that skewness preference of investors is an important driver of various market anomalies. Using a combined measure of mispricing based on 11 prominent anomaly strategies, we show that return predictability associated with the mispricing component of market anomalies is stronger among firms with higher idiosyncratic skewness. The predictability differences are driven by the higher underperformance of high-skewness firms in short anomaly portfolios. Skewness does not affect the performance of long anomaly portfolios. Portfolio holdings data from a retail brokerage firm show that investors with stronger skewness preferences assign relatively larger weights to stocks in short anomaly portfolios.This paper was accepted by Karl Diether, finance.Supplemental Material: The data files and online appendix are available at https://doi.org/10.1287/mnsc.2023.4898.
AB  - This study demonstrates that skewness preference of investors is an important driver of various market anomalies. Using a combined measure of mispricing based on 11 prominent anomaly strategies, we show that return predictability associated with the mispricing component of market anomalies is stronger among firms with higher idiosyncratic skewness. The predictability differences are driven by the higher underperformance of high-skewness firms in short anomaly portfolios. Skewness does not affect the performance of long anomaly portfolios. Portfolio holdings data from a retail brokerage firm show that investors with stronger skewness preferences assign relatively larger weights to stocks in short anomaly portfolios.This paper was accepted by Karl Diether, finance.Supplemental Material: The data files and online appendix are available at https://doi.org/10.1287/mnsc.2023.4898.
